Due to the isolation, the province of Papua is hidden from the world.
There are also strict rules for foreign journalists.
Earlier this year, two French journalists - Franck Escudie and Basile Longchamp - were expelled from the papui for "lack of cooperation with the authorities", despite the fact that they were given such a rare permission to film.
In his election campaign, Phelim Kine, deputy director of the Asian branch of Human Rights Watch, promised to abolish strict rules for journalists and achieve transparency and development, but this never happened.
