Moore's Ford Bridge Massacre: Activists Recall Racist Lynching
The 1948 Ford Mercury passed by by bystanders in Monroe, Georgia, and plowed toward Moore's Ford Bridge.
But before a car with four black passengers and a white driver could reach the bridge, a group of white men with guns blocked its way.
The leader of the group - a middle-aged man in a striped suit - pulled a long cigarette and looked at the windshield of the car.
