This was caused by an electrical failure.
An exact copy was made in its place.
The state counts on the citizens in the defense of the state.
It will support their training.
With financial support for associations that can be used in the defence of the state, with voluntary shooting training or with a team of training trainers, it counts on the substantive intention of the Act on the Preparedness of Citizens to Defend the State.
The Ministry of Defence, which was tasked with processing it by the government, expects it to increase the physical fitness of Czechs and their abilities, which could then be used by the state in crisis situations.
This is according to a proposal prepared by the Ministry.
If the law were passed in the future, the state would spend hundreds of millions of crowns to support the military.
According to its authors, the basic objective of the proposal is to create an effective system that would help increase the readiness of the inhabitants of the Czech Republic to defend the state, outside the performance of conscription and on a voluntary basis.
For example, the state would financially or materially support associations of amateurs, shooters or cynologists and would allow to increase the capabilities of their members.
In return, he would get data on people who are willing to come to the country for help in times of crisis, and on their abilities or material equipment.
There could also be accredited instructors who would help the associations and other interested parties in training or education.
It is also planned to organize discussions with war veterans or people who have behaved heroically.
One of the possible options assumes that a new office would be created, which would be in charge of the administration and coordination of the project.
The authors of the proposal stress that the participation of people should be voluntary and the state would use their abilities only after the declaration of a state of emergency.
"The whole concept must respect the gradual blurring of previously obvious boundaries between the different types of threats," it said, referring to the dangers of so-called hybrid threats.
Ministerial officials noted that it was therefore necessary to focus on supporting the widest possible set of capabilities, not just military ones.
"The basic objective of the project is to create a very broad base that will enable every citizen to respond competently to situations threatening the sovereignty of the state or the lives, health and property of people, to protect themselves or to contribute to the protection of others, and not to make it difficult for the armed forces of the Czech Republic to perform tasks through improper behavior," the project states.
The adoption of the law would bring considerable financial demands.
According to the Ministry, their amount will depend on the chosen variant.
For example, the Office envisages financial support for projects to prepare citizens for the defence of the state up to CZK 100 million.
